textBoxes.content:
Criteria :


1. Calculations for On Time Delivery does not take in consideration Incoterms at the moment.

2. PO Lines under "Inconsistent Dates" tab are not considered on KPI calculations.

3. The conditional formatting for OTD value is like below :
if value is >=0% and <=70% is "Red", 
>70% and <=85% is "Yellow", 
>85% and <=100% is "Green"

formatText.richText: PO Lines # by Received Date Issue
PO Lines # by Received Date Issue
Inconsistent Dates Details

calculatedFields.name: #polines
calculatedFields.expression:
countOver({po_line_quantity},[],PRE_AGG) 
/*total count of PO Lines value supported for % of grand total of po lines */

calculatedFields.name: rec_sort_key
calculatedFields.expression:
parseInt(
concat(
toString(extract('YYYY', {received_date})),
ifelse(
strlen(toString(extract('MM', {received_date}))) = 1,
concat('0', toString(extract('MM', {received_date}))),
toString(extract('MM', {received_date}))
),
ifelse(
strlen(toString(extract('DD', {received_date}))) = 1,
concat('0', toString(extract('DD', {received_date}))),
toString(extract('DD', {received_date}))
)
)
)
